subSubSection.paragraph:
Carapace (
Figs 34–35
) longer than broad. Without eyes or eye-spots. Anterior margin moderately prominent medially, epistome blunt and almost indistinguishable. Chaetotaxy: 20 setae, formula 4 : 4 : 6 : 6 . Three (four) microlyrifissures in ocular zone, two between median and posterior zones.

Coxal area. Manducatory process with 3 setae. Anterior process of coxa I simple, long and apically pointed; medial process straight with some small, blunt protuberances (
Fig. 36
). Pedipalpal coxa with 7 ( 6–8 ) setae, pedal coxa I with 7 ( 7–8 ), II: 6–7 , III: 4 ( 5 ), IV: 6–7 .

